        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "Last year, I was starting my small business online — my hands shaky, my heart racing, my Facebook page barely more than a pixelated dream. I’d stay up late, poking wool into shapes, wondering if anyone would ever trust me with something as sacred as a pet’s memory.",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
